TYPES OF SQL COMMANDS

1. DATA CONTROL LANGUAGE (DCL)
Data Control Language (DCL) consists of the commands used to control access to the data stored in the database.
- GRANT: Grant permission to a user for database access.
- REVOKE: Take back granted permission from a user.

2. TRANSACTION CONTROL LANGUAGE (TCL)
Transaction Control Language (TCL) commands are used to manage the changes made by DML statements.
- COMMIT: To permanently save the transaction.
- ROLLBACK: To undo a transaction.
- SAVEPOINT: To temporarily save a transaction so that you can rollback to that point whenever necessary.

Note: TCL commands are used only for DML commands, while DDL and DCL commands are auto-committed.
