## Optional Clauses in SELECT (Short)

[WHERE] – Filters rows by condition.  
Example:  
SELECT * FROM employees WHERE salary > 50000;

[GROUP BY] – Groups rows for aggregates.  
Example:  
SELECT dept, COUNT(*) FROM employees GROUP BY dept;

[HAVING] – Filters groups (use with GROUP BY).  
Example:  
SELECT dept, AVG(salary) FROM employees GROUP BY dept HAVING AVG(salary) > 60000;

[ORDER BY] – Sorts result rows.  
Example:  
SELECT name, salary FROM employees ORDER BY salary DESC;

[DISTINCT] – Removes duplicate rows.  
Example:  
SELECT DISTINCT dept FROM employees;
